The Togakushi shrine is a [[shrine]] in [[Togakushi, Nagano|Togakushi]], [[Nagano prefecture|Nagano]], [[Japan]]. The Shrine is also part of the in the [[Joshinetsu Kogen National Park]]. There are actually three shrines, known as the lower, middle, and upper shrine, each ca. 2km apart. The approach to the upper shrine is known for its natural beauty, lined with over 300 majestic old [[cedar]] trees.

